quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  2,154,"And say not of those who are slain on God's path that they are Dead; nay, they are Living! But ye understand not"
  2,155,"With somewhat of fear and hunger, and loss of wealth, and lives, and fruits, will we surely prove you: but bear good tidings to the patient"
  2,156,"Who when a mischance chanceth them, say, \"Verily we are God's, and to Him shall we return"
  2,157,"On them shall be blessings from their Lord, and mercy: and these! - they are the rightly guided"
  2,158,"Verily, Safa and Marwah are among the monuments of God: whoever then maketh a pilgrimage to the temple, or visiteth it, shall not be to blame if he go round about them both. And as for him who of his own accord doeth what is good - God is Grateful, Knowing"
  2,159,"They who conceal aught that we have sent down, either of clear proof or of guidance, after what we have so clearly shewn to men in the Book, God shall curse them, and they who curse shall curse them"
  2,160,"But as for those who turn to me, and amend and make known the truth, even unto them will I turn me, for I am He who Turneth, the Merciful"
  2,161,"Verily, they who are infidels and die infidels, - these! upon them shall be the malison of God and of angels and of all men"
  2,162,"Under it shall they remain for ever: their torment shall not be lightened, and God will not even look upon them"
  2,163,"Your God is one God: there is no God but He, the Compassionate, the Merciful"